    <para id="id6300710">You Decide Glossary and Resource List</para>
    <list id="id16266138" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" mark-suffix=")">
      <item>Controversial – multiple conflicting perspectives or opinions.</item>
      <item>Perspectives – point of view of a particular culture, time, group or background.</item>
      <item>Stakeholder – an individual or group with a vested interest related to an issue.</item>
      <item>Democratic Ideals – expressed in the Declaration of Independence: liberty, justice, equality, life, common good, rule by law, pursuit of happiness.</item>
      <item>Public – relating to the community as a whole.</item>
      <item>Position – an individual’s thinking or opinion about an issue.</item>
      <item>Informed Decision – a decision made after liking at different perspectives; based on evidence.</item>
      <item>Rights and Responsibilities – as expressed in the Constitution and Bill of Rights of the United States: Freedom of Speech, Freedom of Religion, Due Process…)</item>
    </list>
