    <para id="id15359814">
      <emphasis effect="bold">Unit Expectations</emphasis>
    </para>
    <list id="id16507056" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
      <item>In a persuasive paper you will:<list id="id16142847" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><item>Select one of the two offered public issues and summarize the background information you found on that issue.</item><item>Explain how your selected issue is related to both the right and responsibilities of citizenship.</item><item>Make an informed decision about the issue and support your decision with convincing reasons.</item></list></item>
      <item>You will also:<list id="id16783236" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><item>Use your graphic organizer to analyze the different points of view on this issue.</item><item>Use your paper and your graphic organizer to discuss your point of view using a panel discussion format.</item></list></item>
    </list>
    <para id="id15678868">
      <link url="">Lesson 1, Step 6 </link>
      <link url="">Lesson 1, Step 7</link>
    </para>
    <para id="id15712672">Step 7: As a class, you will revisit the class’s understandings that were written on the white board, and entered into their journals. Be prepared to discuss how your understanding has changed by writing definitions in your journal. When finished, the lesson will be over! The next lesson explores key democratic ideals, to include rights and responsibilities in the Declaration of Independence and the Constitution. It also asks you to do specific research, and finally asks you to use the APA citation format to cite you sources. </para>
